🚨Eat this salad every day!🚨

1 big ass salad a day filled with nutrient dense ingredients that will be sure to help you feel the difference in your energy levels! Keep your blood sugar low and help aid in weight loss. 

I’m currently trying to lose some weight so I have to be highly aware of my sodium and sugar intake. I’ve cut out white rice and have replaced a lot of my carbs with either the ingredients you see below or other grains. My protein choices have changed from beef to mainly chicken, fish, and leafy greens

Am I still hungry after this?! Fuck yeah! Do I want a burger?! You got it! 😩 but I am eating for a goal so let’s go self discipline 💪🏾

Salad details: 413 cal // 35.3g Protein // 13g Fats // 45.5g Carbs 

Kale 🥬 85g 
Cabbage Mix 🥬 50g 
Carrots 🥕 42g 
Grape Tomatoes 🍅 74g
White Onion 🧅 80g
Beets 🌰 lol they don’t have a beet emoji 58g
Shrooms lol 🍄 85g
Black beans 105g (vegan friends can do black beans and still get a high amount of protein - there’s 24g of protein!!)
Flax Seeds 13g (Forgot to show it oops!)

Mix with a light dressing - non oil based!!

I’ve posted before that I also drink hot water + magnesium sulfate (Calm).. I’ll wait about another hour or so and drink the hot water mix and then stretch mobilize before I sleep. This late night routine helps me to establish a better circadian sleep cycle - I stretch/mobilize in the dark (with candles ☺️) so I’m turning off all electronics and preparing my body + mind for a better sleep

Big Ass Salad 🥗

Here I go with another salad lol don’t just aimlessly put anything into your salad… understand what food is packed with the most nutrients and also complement one another! 

It is true.. have 1 big ass salad a day! I’m serious! Start doing it today! Not only are you eating tons of micronutrients and vitamins all in one meal but because it’s nutrient dense it’s also low calorie for weight loss clients, heart healthy for those suffering from heart complications, those who eat a lot of meat and unaware of their arteries becoming clogged if they aren’t doing detoxes, packed with antioxidants that help fight against cancer cells etc. OMG I can go on and on.. JUST EAT A BIG ASS SALAD TUH-DAY! And then chug some H2O 💦

Ingredients:

🌱Spinach mix
🌱Kale
🌱Sweet potatoes - do not cut the skin off. The skin is the  most nutrient dense part of the potato. I also cooked them prior
🌱Beets
🌱Avocado - only add a small amount.. 1/4 of the avocado I suggest. You want to also add olive oil in your dressing for healthy fat and the almonds. Between the olive oil, almonds and avocado that’s enough healthy fat!
🌱Sun dried tomatoes - buy the dry form.. the sun dried tomatoes in oil usually are packaged with canola and olive oil.
🌱Carrots
🌱Mushrooms - don’t cook the mushrooms too long. Veggies lose more of their natural nutrients under high heat
🌱Sprouts 
🌱Almonds - I blended these and mixed a small amount of Moringa honey in 🤌🏾 gives the salad a lil sweet taste. If you don’t like that flavor leave the honey out.

use a olive oil - not milked based dressing and DONT PUT TOO MUCH SALAD DRESSING😬 enjoy!

When you cook with whole natural foods that God has provided us with you can never go wrong! Plant based ingredients address a ton of underlying issues from the every day flu to something a lil more serious 🤕
Remember to keep your sodium low and enjoy this on a cold day at home 🖤🖤🖤

Ingredients : lol y’all I’m black we don’t measure our ingredients 😂 I’ll do better next time tho my bad
🥕 Carrots
🥒 Celery (they didn’t have a celery emoji ☹️)
🍄 Mushrooms
🧄 Garlic
🥬 Cabbage
🍅 Crushed red tomatoes 
🫒 Virgin olive oil to cook with
🌶️ Spices - Cumin, Tumeric, Pepper, Pink salt, Oregano, Paprika, A tad of Cayenne Pepper 

🌱Cook the aromatics first (carrots, celery, mushrooms, and garlic) let them get slightly tender but not super soft

🌱Add in all your spices.. taste it now to see if your like the flavor just don’t go overboard with your seasonings.. remember sodium intake is fine but too much defeats the purpose, especially if you aren’t highly active

🌱Now add the can of crushed red tomatoes, and low sodium veggie broth! Please buy a low sodium one.. remember you already added some sodium with the spices. The one I used had 120mg of sodium

🌱Add the cabbage in bunches and submerge it into the soup

🌱Bring everything to a boil first then turn the fire to low and let it simmer for about 20-30min

Enjoy😋
